// Example planet rotation (Q-2026-07-10-B): SpinSet sets the world frame's
// angular velocity (radians per simulated second, either sign). From its
// stamped tick on, every active particle feels the Coriolis deflection —
// trajectories curve, and coherent vortices can emerge where straight-line
// drift would have dispersed. Energy is untouched (the deflection does no
// work); total momentum keeps its magnitude and rotates.
//
//   genesis run    --actions scripts/spin-up.ron
//   genesis verify --actions scripts/spin-up.ron
//
// Spin up early, reverse later, stop at the end — three eras with distinct
// dynamics in one run.
(
    actions: [
        (
            tick: 200,
            action: SpinSet(spin: 0.4),
        ),
        (
            tick: 2000,
            action: SpinSet(spin: -0.4),
        ),
        (
            tick: 3800,
            action: SpinSet(spin: 0.0),
        ),
    ],
)
